# Enforce LF line endings everywhere in the repo, regardless of the
# contributor's OS. SvelteKit, Vite, Prettier, ESLint, Node, and the
# GitHub Pages build runner all expect LF; mixed line endings cause
# spurious diffs on Windows checkouts and occasional tooling breakage.
# https://git-scm.com/docs/gitattributes

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binary overrides so Git never tries to diff or normalise
# these — auto-detection is reliable but pinning the common formats
# guards against edge cases.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.webp  binary
*.ico   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.eot   binary
*.otf   binary
*.zip   binary
*.gz    binary
*.pdf   binary
*.parquet binary
